    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - REAR HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="9">
        <title>REAR HOUSING</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302549">Figure 49</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302549" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302549" filename="../figg13/G1302549.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 49. Rear Housing Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the rear housing in a vise as shown (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302550">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302550" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302550" filename="../figg13/G1302550.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 50. Position Rear Housing in Vise</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar to drive the output shaft bearing from the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302551">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302551" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302551" filename="../figg13/G1302551.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 51. Drive Output Shaft Bearing From Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove snap rings from the rear countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302552">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302552" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302552" filename="../figg13/G1302552.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Remove Snap Rings From Rear Countershafts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear countershafts and bearings from the rear plate by driving the shafts to the rear
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302553">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302553" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302553" filename="../figg13/G1302553.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Remove Rear Countershafts and Bearings From Rear Plate</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block the countershaft bearings and press them from the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302554">Figure 54</hotlnk>). Remove the inner snap ring (inset) if so equipped.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302554" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302554" filename="../figg13/G1302554.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Press Countershaft Bearings From Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and retainer plates from the idler shafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302555">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302555" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302555" filename="../figg13/G1302555.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Remove Bolts and Retainer Plates From Idler Shafts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler shafts and reverse idler gears from the rear housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302556">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302556" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302556" filename="../figg13/G1302556.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Remove Idler Shafts and Reverse Idler Gears</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the O-rings from the idler shafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302557">left, Figure 57</hotlnk>) and two sets of roller bearings from the idler gears
                (right).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302557" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302557" filename="../figg13/G1302557.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Remove O-Rings From Idler Shafts</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
